  "text": "One crucial step of this operationalized framework is the aggregation of indicators within and the criticality points between three separate dimensions to an overall sum of LCSA criticality points in order to support decision makers in their assessment. Depending on which aggregation logic is applied, these changes in criticality points could result in a change of the overall LCSA criticality points giving decision makers the clear indication that the evaluated improvement measure would contribute to the overall improvement of product sustainability. This challenge is addressed by [CITATION_1] through the introduction of weights to the sustainability dimensions. However, in a business context, an increase in costs would most likely lead to the rejection of the improvement measure for component B. Here, the concept of monetization, and the Product Sustainability Budget in particular, offers a solution.",
  "correct_citation": {
